&lt;p&gt;Shopmonkey is looking for a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Product Manager&lt;/strong&gt; to join our dynamic team, help us build the next generation of our platform, and lead to a dedicated squad of product, design, and engineering individuals. At Shopmonkey, we&#39;re not just building software; we&#39;re on a mission to help every auto repair shop thrive. We believe that with the right tools, shop owners can run their businesses smarter, faster, and more profitably. We are a fast-paced, collaborative, and customer-obsessed team, and we&#39;re looking for a senior product leader who shares our passion for getting under the hood and solving real-world problems.&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Please note for any candidates in the San Francisco Bay area, this is a hybrid role with 2-3 days per week on-site at our Morgan Hill, CA office to collaborate and stay connected.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll define and evangelize product needs for our core customers, representing Product in customer engagements and partnering closely with customer-facing teams to deliver maximum value. Your ability to communicate prioritization decisions, technical nuances, and the voice of the customer will impact thousands of auto shops across North America.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique role that requires an organized, impact-oriented, and customer- and product-focused individual who is comfortable with ambiguity, takes initiative, and builds strong, collaborative relationships across teams and with customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Define Product Strategy: &lt;/strong&gt;Define and champion the strategic direction, product vision, and roadmap for your squad, aligning with overall company goals and objectives. Stay attuned to industry trends, competitive dynamics, and emerging technologies that influence our space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive Execution: &lt;/strong&gt;Lead feature scoping, prioritization, and trade-off discussions — knowing when to say no to achieve the best outcomes. Translate vision into clear product requirements and user stories, managing the backlog to ensure maximum impact and alignment with company goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Lead Cross-Functional Teams:&lt;/strong&gt; lead, inspire, and collaborate with engineering, design, marketing, and customer-facing teams to ensure successful launches, adoption, and measurable outcomes. Work with leadership to connect strategic plans to actionable, prioritized initiatives with clear metrics and timelines.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate Across Squads&lt;/strong&gt;: Collaborate closely with other squad leads and stakeholders to coordinate efforts, resolve dependencies, and optimize resource allocation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Champion the Customer: &lt;/strong&gt;Conduct research, analyze data, and synthesize insights to deeply understand the needs of our diverse customers — from small independent shops to multi-location enterprises. Use these customer insights and data analytics to guide decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Own the Full Lifecycle: &lt;/strong&gt;Oversee the end-to-end product lifecycle — from ideation and validation through launch, iteration, and optimization. Measure success using product metrics such as adoption, engagement, and customer satisfaction, and use these to guide continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
